1.text: Read the following sentences paying attention to the highlighted words.

2.text: Why don't you sit down and make yourselves comfortable, so that we can start our discussion straightaway?
2.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Why don't you sit down and make yourselves comfortable, so that we can start our discussion straightaway?</prosody></speak>

3.text: Did you do it all by yourself?
3.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Did you do it all by yourself?</prosody></speak>

5.text: Our art teacher himself designed the invitation for the Chief Guest.
5.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Our art teacher himself designed the invitation for the Chief Guest.</prosody></speak>

6.text: Ruvin and Meena promised to do the decorations by themselves.
6.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'><phoneme alphabet='ipa' ph='rovin'>Ruvin</phoneme> and Meena promised to do the decorations by themselves.</prosody></speak>

7.text: Our English teacher said that she herself would prepare them.
7.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Our English teacher said that she herself would prepare them.</prosody></speak>

8.text: I'm sure we can make the English camp a success and be proud of ourselves.
